---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import KineticHero from "../components/KineticHero.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Robin van Baalen" description="Almost thirty years building software. AI, bleeding edge tools, and an obsession with the details that shape how software feels.">
  <KineticHero>
    I build because I love it.
  </KineticHero>

  <div class="max-w-xl space-y-6">
    <p class="text-lg text-primary leading-relaxed">
      I've been building software for almost thirty years — it's my work, my passion, and my hobby. The tools keep getting better, and right now they're moving faster than ever.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-primary leading-relaxed">
      AI redefined what a single builder can ship. I use it every day, stay on the bleeding edge, and build things that weren't possible a year ago. But what hasn't changed is what I care about: the details. The tiniest transition, the spacing between elements, the right color scheme — that's not polish, that's the product.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
